-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 24.1023 percent
-- 
-- Fri Jul 04, 2014 01:46PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, July 4 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said the yield on its 91-day bill rose to a fresh three-year high of 24.1023 percent at Friday's auction, from 24.0892 percent at the last sale.

The Bank said it accepted 450.19 million cedis ($136 million) worth of bids out of the 450.32 million worth of bids tendered for the 91-day paper. For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201387.pdf